**CORPFIT**

*Circle of Resilient People*

**QUANTUM Content Factory**

Daily Operations Guide

*How the system works, what you do, and where to find everything*

February 2026

**1. How the System Works**

The QUANTUM Content Factory is a fully automated system that discovers
trending wellness topics, creates video content scripts, and produces
videos. It runs every morning at 9:00 AM Cairo time. Your only job is to
review and approve content from your phone.

**1.1 The Daily Pipeline (What Happens Automatically)**

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **E1 Trend Scout discovers fresh trends** *9:00 AM*             |
| *1 |                                                                 |
| ** | At 9:00 AM Cairo, E1 automatically scans wellness trend sources |
|    | (Google Trends, TikTok trending, fitness blogs) and finds 7-15  |
|    | fresh topics. It scores each trend by relevance and maps them   |
|    | to CorpFit modules (Steps, Workouts, Meals, Check-in, Events).  |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **QUANTUM creates 3 content briefs** *\~9:02 AM*                |
| *2 |                                                                 |
| ** | Immediately after E1 finishes, QUANTUM reads the trend board,   |
|    | checks what content already exists (no duplicates), and creates |
|    | 3 unique briefs. Each brief has a topic, module, platform       |
|    | (TikTok/Instagram/LinkedIn), funnel (B2C/B2B), and duration.    |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **Briefs arrive on Telegram** *\~9:04 AM*                       |
| *3 |                                                                 |
| ** | You receive 3 briefs on Telegram with full details: topic,      |
|    | module, platform, funnel, duration, trend score, and suggested  |
|    | angle. Each brief has Approve and Reject buttons.               |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

**Everything above happens without you doing anything. Now it\'s your
turn:**

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **You tap Approve on Telegram** *You decide*                    |
| *4 |                                                                 |
| ** | Review the brief on your phone. If the topic looks good, tap    |
|    | Approve. If not, tap Reject and it\'s archived. You can approve |
|    | all 3, just 1, or none.                                         |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **E2 generates full content (automatic)** *\~30 seconds*        |
| *5 |                                                                 |
| ** | Within 30 seconds of your Approve tap, ELECTRON-2 generates the |
|    | complete content package: 3 hooks, a timed script, on-screen    |
|    | text, storyboard, short caption, long caption, CTA, and         |
|    | disclaimer. It runs through 3 AI quality gates checking for     |
|    | health claims, brand tone, and audience fit.                    |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **Content preview appears on Telegram** *Automatic*             |
| *6 |                                                                 |
| ** | The FULL generated content appears on Telegram so you can read  |
|    | every word the audience will see. At the bottom: Publish and    |
|    | Kill buttons. This is your quality check.                       |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **You tap Publish or Kill** *You decide*                        |
| *7 |                                                                 |
| ** | Read the content. If it\'s good, tap Publish. If something\'s   |
|    | off, tap Kill and it\'s archived. You\'re the final quality     |
|    | gate.                                                           |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+
| *  | **E3 produces the video (automatic)** *\~2-5 minutes*           |
| *8 |                                                                 |
| ** | After you tap Publish, ELECTRON-3 automatically selects the     |
|    | right video tool (Veo for cinematic, Kling for fast clips,      |
|    | HeyGen for B2B avatars) and produces the video. A preview       |
|    | appears on Telegram.                                            |
+----+-----------------------------------------------------------------+

**2. Your Daily Routine**

This is what your typical day looks like as the content operator:

**2.1 Morning (9:00-9:15 AM Cairo)**

📱 Check Telegram around 9:05 AM --- 3 new briefs should be waiting

👀 Review each brief\'s topic, module, and platform

✅ Tap Approve on the ones you like

❌ Tap Reject on any you don\'t want

⏳ Wait \~30 seconds for content to generate

📋 Read the full content preview that appears

🚀 Tap Publish if content looks good

💀 Tap Kill if something\'s wrong

**2.2 Anytime (Monitoring)**

📊 Type /status in Telegram --- get system health dashboard

⏰ Type /stale in Telegram --- see briefs waiting too long

🌐 Open dashboard.corpfit.cloud --- full mission control

**2.3 That\'s It**

**The entire system runs itself. You only need 10-15 minutes per day to
review and approve content. Everything else is automated.**

**3. Telegram Actions Reference**

Every action happens through Telegram buttons or commands. Here\'s the
complete list:

**3.1 Button Actions**

  ------------ ---------- ------------------------ -------------------------
  **Button**   **When**   **What Happens**         **Next Step**

  **✅         Stage 1    Brief status changes to  Wait 30s for content
  Approve**               \'approved\'. E2 starts  preview to appear
                          generating content       
                          automatically.           

  **❌         Stage 1    Brief is archived.       Done --- brief is gone
  Reject**                Nothing is generated.    

  **✅         Stage 2    Content is marked        Wait 2-5 min for video
  Publish**               \'published\'. E3 starts preview
                          video production         
                          automatically.           

  **❌ Kill**  Stage 2    Content is archived. No  Done --- content is gone
                          video is produced.       
  ------------ ---------- ------------------------ -------------------------

**3.2 Telegram Commands**

  ------------- ------------------------------- ---------------------------
  **Command**   **What It Does**                **When to Use**

  **/status**   Shows complete system health:   Anytime you want to check
                how many trends, briefs,        if the system is running
                content pieces, videos, errors, 
                and when each part last ran.    

  **/stale**    Lists any briefs that have been When you want to clean up
                pending or approved for more    old briefs
                than 24 hours without action.   
